cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for handling sparse depth data in vision applications. The paper focuses on depth completion and semantic segmentation, which are both subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of CNNs for robotics applications (cs.RO) and machine learning techniques for feature learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks for classification tasks (cs.AI) and the optimization of network parameters (cs.NE).
